In the past it's been found that JIRA simply does not function well with Symmantec anti virus, it's noted down [in this page for performance  under *Anti Virus*|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/Crashes+and+Performance+Issues+Troubleshooting] but nowhere else. 
{quote}
Symantec must be uninstalled - painful experience has proven that even stopping the services does not prevent it slowing JIRA down.
{quote}

The problem with this is that many customers go ahead and install JIRA but have no idea that this is not going to work for them - they have a wide range of performance problems and also erratic and unpredictable behaviour from the web app.

It would be more upfront with them if a warning about the Symmantec anti virus was to be put on our Supported platforms page, as customers would look here first before installing JIRA: [https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Supported+Platforms]

