Via REST API, when there is the need to add a new issue with remote links, I would like to make ONE call to:

{noformat}
POST /issue/{issueIdOrKey}
{noformat}

instead of calling the TWO:

{noformat}
POST /issue/{issueIdOrKey}
POST /issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink
{noformat}

The reason for this is that I do not want people to get notified two times: the first time for issue creation, the second time for link addition.

In my opinion, it is useless for people to get notified twice when I already have the link to add at creation time.

Another way of doing this would be the ability to suppress notifications for certain calls (or maybe any?) for batch tasks like this one, like adding a parameter during post. ie. 

{noformat}
POST /issue/{issueIdOrKey}/remotelink?suppressNotification=1
{noformat}

