In our organisation many 'project leads' manage their projects, i.e. setting versions, defining components and taking care of roles (under People). There are several processes supported by JIRA, with different settings (e.g. bug tracking, Agile development).

No matter how often the admins say it, project leads keep assigning roles to people that are irrelevant to their process/project; i.e. the roles don't appear in the permission scheme linked to that project, so it makes no sense using them - or on the other hand they forget to use the right roles and then complain that 'it doesn't work'. I guess this should sound familiar to  some users.

I checked with Atlassian ([SUPPORT] (JSP-127325)) if it is possible, but no, so this is the feature request: please make it possible (e.g. generic, via sysadmins; or per project via project lead; or both) to show/use only those roles that are relevant according to the permission scheme of that project. Thanks!

